# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# Example: feat(button): add size variants to Button component
#
# Types:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#
# Scope:
#   Optional, can be anything specifying the place of the commit change
#   Examples: button, dialog, core, cli, etc.
#
# Subject:
#   Brief summary of the change in present tense. Not capitalized. No period at the end.
#
# Body:
#   Optional. Detailed description of the change.
#   Use present tense. Include motivation and contrasts with previous behavior.
#
# Footer:
#   Optional. Reference issues being closed.
#   Example: Closes #123, #456 